  "title": "Gracie the Giraffe Was Missing 2 Weeks in Texas",
  "script": "A giraffe just vanished? Gracie, a 3-year-old reticulated giraffe at Cedar Hollow Ranch in the Texas Hill Country, wandered through an open gate — and kept walking. For nearly 2 weeks, her owner sent helicopters searching 7,500 acres of rugged terrain. No luck. So he offered a $5,000 reward. A few scattered sightings came in. The helicopters kept circling. Meanwhile, Gracie was apparently doing just fine — hanging out near a pond about 4 miles from home, swishing her tail, surrounded by trees growing from rock formations. She weighed at least 1,200 pounds and was in no rush to go anywhere. Aerial crews finally spotted her Friday near the town of Leakey. So how exactly do you lose a 1,200-pound giraffe for 2 weeks?",
